Ingredients.1: 1 (9 inch) unbaked deep-dish pie crust, at room temperature

Ingredients.5: 3 fluid ounces cinnamon whiskey (such as Fireball®)

Directions.1: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).

Directions.2: Evenly pierce entire pie crust with a fork.

Directions.3: Bake crust in the preheated oven until golden brown, about 12 minutes. Remove from the oven; increase oven temperature to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).

Directions.4: Combine pumpkin pie filling, evaporated milk, sugar, whiskey, eggs, salt, ginger, cloves, and cinnamon in a large bowl; beat with an electric mixer until just blended. Pour into the pre-baked pie crust.

Directions.5: Return to the preheated oven and bake pie for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and continue baking until filling is set and no longer jiggles, and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 45 minutes.

Directions.6: Remove from the oven and let cool to room temperature before serving, about 2 hours.
